From: dimos
Date: 2026-05-09
Subject: [PATCH] EglPBufferSupport: fall back to mesa surfaceless when DRM init fails

OGRE-Next 2.3's EGL_HEADLESS path enumerates physical DRM devices via
eglQueryDevicesEXT and tries eglGetPlatformDisplay(EGL_PLATFORM_DEVICE_EXT)
on each. On systems where the only DRM device is one mesa cannot drive
(e.g. Nvidia desktops without nouveau, or any box with a single GPU
mesa rejects), this fails with "Not allowed to force software rendering
when API explicitly selects a hardware device" and headless rendering
is impossible.

mesa exposes a vendor-neutral surfaceless platform via
EGL_MESA_platform_surfaceless (eglGetPlatformDisplay with
EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA = 0x31DD) which doesn't require any DRM
device — it uses llvmpipe / swrast directly. Fall back to it when the
DRM-device path fails.

--- a/RenderSystems/GL3Plus/src/windowing/EGL/PBuffer/OgreEglPBufferSupport.cpp
+++ b/RenderSystems/GL3Plus/src/windowing/EGL/PBuffer/OgreEglPBufferSupport.cpp
@@ -304,21 +304,33 @@ namespace Ogre
         deviceData.eglDisplay =
             eglGetPlatformDisplay( EGL_PLATFORM_DEVICE_EXT, mDevices[deviceIdx], attribs );

-        EGL_CHECK_ERROR
-
-        if( deviceData.eglDisplay == EGL_NO_DISPLAY )
-        {
-            OGRE_EXCEPT( Exception::ERR_RENDERINGAPI_ERROR,
-                         "eglGetPlatformDisplay failed for device " + deviceData.name,
-                         "EGLSupport::getGLDisplay" );
-        }
-
         EGLint major = 0, minor = 0;
-        if( eglInitialize( deviceData.eglDisplay, &major, &minor ) == EGL_FALSE )
+        const bool deviceInit =
+            ( deviceData.eglDisplay != EGL_NO_DISPLAY ) &&
+            ( eglInitialize( deviceData.eglDisplay, &major, &minor ) == EGL_TRUE );
+
+        if( !deviceInit )
         {
-            OGRE_EXCEPT( Exception::ERR_RENDERINGAPI_ERROR,
-                         "eglInitialize failed for device " + deviceData.name,
-                         "EGLSupport::getGLDisplay" );
+            // Fall back to mesa's surfaceless platform — no DRM device
+            // required, uses llvmpipe / swrast. This is the path that
+            // works on systems where the only enumerated DRM device is
+            // one mesa can't drive (e.g. Nvidia-only desktops).
+            const EGLint kEGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA = 0x31DD;
+            LogManager::getSingleton().logMessage(
+                "Device init failed for " + deviceData.name +
+                ", trying EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA fallback" );
+            deviceData.eglDisplay = eglGetPlatformDisplay(
+                kEGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA, EGL_DEFAULT_DISPLAY, attribs );
+            if( deviceData.eglDisplay == EGL_NO_DISPLAY ||
+                eglInitialize( deviceData.eglDisplay, &major, &minor ) == EGL_FALSE )
+            {
+                OGRE_EXCEPT(
+                    Exception::ERR_RENDERINGAPI_ERROR,
+                    "eglInitialize failed for device " + deviceData.name +
+                        " AND EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA fallback also failed; "
+                        "no usable EGL display",
+                    "EGLSupport::getGLDisplay" );
+            }
         }

         EGL_CHECK_ERROR
